<Defs>

    <ThingDef ParentName="AnimalThingBase">
        <defName>MLW_Aurochs</defName>
        <label>aurochs</label>
        <description>A wild ancestor to the domestic cow, brought back from extinction through a combination of cloning, selective breeding, and genetic manipulation, and identifiable by its large size, massive horns, and curly, blonde forehead hair.\n\nIn human culture, aurochs appear prominently, usually as symbols of strength and vitality. Aurochs hunts are widely represented throughout history, and downing an aurochs is seen in many cultures as a demonstration of strength and valour. Their horns are especially prized, and are used in religious offerings or as trophies or drinking cups.\n\nIn many hopeful settlements, the aurochs' strength and hardiness is particularly valued and has seen it used as a draught or pack animal. In contrast with regular cattle however, aurochs are generally inefficient for milk production, and are instead usually kept for meat.</description>
